                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/1643: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-06T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 6, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 6—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. A Government communiqué has been published to the effect that in view of the
                    fact that trade relations between Manchukuo and Siam have been firmly
                    established the Government has recognized the State of Manchukuo in a telegram
                    sent to the Prime Minister of Manchukuo by the Siamese Prime Minister.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
